article.headline: N. Arizona 70, N. Dakota St. 58
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Mike Felt scored 17 points and North Dakota State easily extended its season-opening winning streak to three games with a 70-58 victory against Northern Arizona on Sunday. TrayVonn Wright added 13 points, six rebounds, three blocks and two steals for North Dakota State, which swept all three of its games in the Hilltop Challenge. The Bison shot 75 percent in the first half while opening up a 21-point lead by intermission. Marshall Bjorklund went 4 for 4 while scoring 11 points and grabbing five rebounds for North Dakota State. Danny Cheek had 10 points -- all in the second half -- for Northern Arizona, which lost all three games in the tournament.
